   "source": [
    "# 👶 SmartBabyScale - Machine Learning Pipeline\n",
    "### Complete Preprocessing, Training, Validation, and Serialization Workflow\n",
    "\n",
    "This Jupyter Notebook contains the complete machine learning workflow for training risk classification models for the **SmartBabyScale** system. \n",
    "\n",
    "### 🏥 Clinical Context: SNAPPE-II\n",
    "The **SNAPPE-II** (Score for Neonatal Acute Physiology with Perinatal Extension-II) is a validated clinical scoring system used in Neonatal Intensive Care Units (NICUs) to assess illness severity and predict mortality. The score ranges from **0 to 162**, where higher scores indicate a higher probability of mortality. It comprises:\n",
    "1. **6 physiological parameters** (representing acute physiology instability collected within 12 hours of admission).\n",
    "2. **3 perinatal extension parameters** (birth weight, low Apgar score, and Small for Gestational Age status).\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🤖 Machine Learning Infrastructure Overview\n",
    "To deploy this model on a **Raspberry Pi** edge device, we train two distinct architectures:\n",
    "1. **Support Vector Machine (SVM)** with a Radial Basis Function (RBF) kernel: Excellent for establishing non-linear separating boundaries on low-to-medium dimensional tabular data.\n",
    "2. **Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP)** Feedforward Neural Network: Learns complex hierarchical feature representations via backpropagation.\n",
    "\n",
    "Both models are trained to predict the probability of **mortality risk** based on vital signs (sensors) and static demographic inputs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🛠️ Step 1: Import Dependencies & Core Setup\n",
    "We use standard scientific Python libraries (`numpy`, `pandas`, `matplotlib`) alongside `scikit-learn` for preprocessing, modeling, and evaluation. `joblib` is used to serialize the trained artifacts for edge deployment."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import joblib\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Model Preprocessing and Data Splitting\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "\n",
    "# Classification Models\n",
    "from sklearn.svm import SVC\n",
    "from sklearn.neural_network import MLPClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "# Diagnostic and Performance Evaluation Metrics\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, roc_auc_score,\n",
    "    classification_report, confusion_matrix, roc_curve, auc\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set random seed for reproducibility across dataset generation and model splits\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "print(\"System packages successfully imported and random seed established.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ⚖️ Step 2: Clinical Data Simulation (SNAPPE-II Ground Truth)\n",
    "\n",
    "Since clinical infant datasets are highly protected, we simulate 5,000 realistic neonatal patient sessions. \n",
    "\n",
    "Rather than generating completely random values (which would lack clinical correlation), we define three severity bands:\n",
    "- **Low Severity (70% of cases)**: Represents stable, healthy neonates. Typically normal heart rate, high SpO2, and normal temperature.\n",
    "- **Moderate Severity (22% of cases)**: Neonates with mild distress or prematurity, exhibiting slightly altered vitals.\n",
    "- **High Severity (8% of cases)**: Critical conditions (e.g., extreme prematurity, sepsis). Characterized by hypothermia, hypoxia, and low birth weights.\n",
    "\n",
    "We calculate the true clinical **SNAPPE-II score** for each patient, then apply a sigmoidal logit curve to determine the probability of mortality:\n",
    "$$\\text{logit} = -4.0 + 0.08 \\times \\text{SNAPPE-II}$$ \n",
    "$$P(\\text{mortality}) = \\frac{1}{1 + e^{-\\text{logit}}}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_snappe_ii(row):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Calculates the SNAPPE-II score according to clinical definitions.\n",
    "    The final score ranges from 0 (perfect health) to 162 (most critical).\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Point Scoring Mechanics:\n",
    "    - Birth Weight (g): < 750g (17 pts), 750-999g (10 pts), >= 1000g (0 pts)\n",
    "    - Small for Gestational Age (SGA): Yes (5 pts), No (0 pts)\n",
    "    - Apgar Score at 5 minutes: < 7 (18 pts), >= 7 (0 pts)\n",
    "    - Mean Blood Pressure (mmHg): < 20 (19 pts), 20-29 (9 pts), >= 30 (0 pts)\n",
    "    - Lowest Temp (Celsius): < 35.0 C (15 pts), 35.0-35.6 C (8 pts), > 35.6 C (0 pts)\n",
    "    - PO2 / FiO2 Ratio: < 0.3 (28 pts), 0.3-0.99 (16 pts), 1.0-2.49 (5 pts), >= 2.5 (0 pts)\n",
    "    - Lowest Serum pH: < 7.10 (16 pts), 7.10-7.19 (7 pts), >= 7.20 (0 pts)\n",
    "    - Multiple Seizures: Present (19 pts), Absent (0 pts)\n",
    "    - Urine Output (mL/kg/hr): < 0.1 (18 pts), 0.1-0.9 (5 pts), >= 1.0 (0 pts)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    score = 0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # 1. Birth Weight (Demographic Constant)\n",
    "    weight = row['birth_weight_g']\n",
    "    if weight < 750:\n",
    "        score += 17\n",
    "    elif 750 <= weight < 1000:\n",
    "        score += 10\n",
    "        \n",
    "    # 2. Small for Gestational Age (SGA - Demographic Constant)\n",
    "    if row['sga'] == 1:\n",
    "        score += 5\n",
    "        \n",
    "    # 3. Apgar Score (Perinatal Constant)\n",
    "    if row['apgar_score_5min'] < 7:\n",
    "        score += 18\n",
    "        \n",
    "    # 4. Mean Blood Pressure (Clinical Input)\n",
    "    mbp = row['mean_blood_pressure']\n",
    "    if mbp < 20:\n",
    "        score += 19\n",
    "    elif 20 <= mbp < 30:\n",
    "        score += 9\n",
    "        \n",
    "    # 5. Lowest Temperature (Infrared Sensor mlx90614 minimum value)\n",
    "    temp = row['lowest_temperature_celsius']\n",
    "    if temp < 35.0:\n",
    "        score += 15\n",
    "    elif 35.0 <= temp <= 35.6:\n",
    "        score += 8\n",
    "        \n",
    "    # 6. PO2 / FiO2 Ratio (Clinical Input)\n",
    "    po2_fio2 = row['po2_fio2_ratio']\n",
    "    if po2_fio2 < 0.3:\n",
    "        score += 28\n",
    "    elif 0.3 <= po2_fio2 < 1.0:\n",
    "        score += 16\n",
    "    elif 1.0 <= po2_fio2 < 2.5:\n",
    "        score += 5\n",
    "        \n",
    "    # 7. Lowest Serum pH (Clinical Lab Input)\n",
    "    ph = row['lowest_serum_ph']\n",
    "    if ph < 7.10:\n",
    "        score += 16\n",
    "    elif 7.10 <= ph < 7.20:\n",
    "        score += 7\n",
    "        \n",
    "    # 8. Multiple Seizures (Clinical Observation)\n",
    "    if row['seizures'] == 1:\n",
    "        score += 19\n",
    "        \n",
    "    # 9. Urine Output (Nursing Intake/Output measurement)\n",
    "    uo = row['urine_output_ml_kg_hr']\n",
    "    if uo < 0.1:\n",
    "        score += 18\n",
    "    elif 0.1 <= uo < 1.0:\n",
    "        score += 5\n",
    "        \n",
    "    return score\n",
    "\n",
    "def generate_dataset(num_samples=5000):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Generates synthetic medical records of NICU patients with realistic correlations.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    data = []\n",
    "    for i in range(num_samples):\n",
    "        # Choose severity tier based on normal NICU admission demographics\n",
    "        severity = np.random.choice(['low', 'moderate', 'high'], p=[0.70, 0.22, 0.08])\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Generate clinical values dependent on the patient's severity category\n",
    "        if severity == 'high':\n",
    "            # Critical pre-term neonate\n",
    "            gestational_age_weeks = int(np.random.normal(26, 2))\n",
    "            birth_weight_g = float(np.random.normal(700, 150))\n",
    "            sga = np.random.choice([0, 1], p=[0.7, 0.3])\n",
    "            apgar_score_5min = int(np.random.choice([3, 4, 5, 6, 7], p=[0.2, 0.3, 0.3, 0.1, 0.1]))\n",
    "            mean_blood_pressure = float(np.random.normal(18, 4))\n",
    "            lowest_temperature_celsius = float(np.random.normal(34.2, 1.2))\n",
    "            po2_fio2_ratio = float(np.random.exponential(0.25))  # Highly skewed low ratios\n",
    "            lowest_serum_ph = float(np.random.normal(7.02, 0.1))\n",
    "            seizures = np.random.choice([0, 1], p=[0.6, 0.4])\n",
    "            urine_output_ml_kg_hr = float(np.random.exponential(0.3))\n",
    "            avg_heart_rate_bpm = float(np.random.normal(165, 15))\n",
    "            lowest_spo2_percent = float(np.random.normal(83, 6))\n",
    "        elif severity == 'moderate':\n",
    "            # Moderate risk neonate with mild distress\n",
    "            gestational_age_weeks = int(np.random.normal(32, 2))\n",
    "            birth_weight_g = float(np.random.normal(1500, 300))\n",
    "            sga = np.random.choice([0, 1], p=[0.8, 0.2])\n",
    "            apgar_score_5min = int(np.random.choice([5, 6, 7, 8], p=[0.1, 0.3, 0.4, 0.2]))\n",
    "            mean_blood_pressure = float(np.random.normal(26, 5))\n",
    "            lowest_temperature_celsius = float(np.random.normal(35.2, 0.8))\n",
    "            po2_fio2_ratio = float(np.random.normal(1.5, 0.6))\n",
    "            lowest_serum_ph = float(np.random.normal(7.15, 0.07))\n",
    "            seizures = np.random.choice([0, 1], p=[0.9, 0.1])\n",
    "            urine_output_ml_kg_hr = float(np.random.normal(0.8, 0.4))\n",
    "            avg_heart_rate_bpm = float(np.random.normal(148, 10))\n",
    "            lowest_spo2_percent = float(np.random.normal(92, 4))\n",
    "        else: \n",
    "            # Healthy term neonate\n",
    "            gestational_age_weeks = int(np.random.normal(38, 2))\n",
    "            birth_weight_g = float(np.random.normal(3100, 400))\n",
    "            sga = np.random.choice([0, 1], p=[0.95, 0.05])\n",
    "            apgar_score_5min = int(np.random.choice([7, 8, 9, 10], p=[0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.1]))\n",
    "            mean_blood_pressure = float(np.random.normal(38, 6))\n",
    "            lowest_temperature_celsius = float(np.random.normal(36.6, 0.3))\n",
    "            po2_fio2_ratio = float(np.random.normal(3.2, 0.5))\n",
    "            lowest_serum_ph = float(np.random.normal(7.35, 0.05))\n",
    "            seizures = np.random.choice([0, 1], p=[0.99, 0.01])\n",
    "            urine_output_ml_kg_hr = float(np.random.normal(2.0, 0.6))\n",
    "            avg_heart_rate_bpm = float(np.random.normal(138, 8))\n",
    "            lowest_spo2_percent = float(np.random.normal(97, 2))\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Bound constraints to enforce physical boundaries\n",
    "        gestational_age_weeks = max(22, min(42, gestational_age_weeks))\n",
    "        birth_weight_g = max(400.0, birth_weight_g)\n",
    "        mean_blood_pressure = max(5.0, min(80.0, mean_blood_pressure))\n",
    "        lowest_temperature_celsius = max(28.0, min(41.0, lowest_temperature_celsius))\n",
    "        po2_fio2_ratio = max(0.05, po2_fio2_ratio)\n",
    "        lowest_serum_ph = max(6.5, min(7.6, lowest_serum_ph))\n",
    "        urine_output_ml_kg_hr = max(0.0, urine_output_ml_kg_hr)\n",
    "        avg_heart_rate_bpm = max(60.0, min(230.0, avg_heart_rate_bpm))\n",
    "        lowest_spo2_percent = max(40.0, min(100.0, lowest_spo2_percent))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        row = {\n",
    "            'patient_id': 1000 + i,\n",
    "            'birth_weight_g': round(birth_weight_g, 1),\n",
    "            'gestational_age_weeks': gestational_age_weeks,\n",
    "            'sga': sga,\n",
    "            'apgar_score_5min': apgar_score_5min,\n",
    "            'mean_blood_pressure': round(mean_blood_pressure, 1),\n",
    "            'lowest_temperature_celsius': round(lowest_temperature_celsius, 2),\n",
    "            'po2_fio2_ratio': round(po2_fio2_ratio, 2),\n",
    "            'lowest_serum_ph': round(lowest_serum_ph, 2),\n",
    "            'seizures': seizures,\n",
    "            'urine_output_ml_kg_hr': round(urine_output_ml_kg_hr, 2),\n",
    "            'avg_heart_rate_bpm': round(avg_heart_rate_bpm, 1),\n",
    "            'lowest_spo2_percent': int(lowest_spo2_percent)\n",
    "        }\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Calculate dynamic clinical SNAPPE-II score\n",
    "        row['snappe_score'] = calculate_snappe_ii(row)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Apply Sigmoidal Logistic Probability Curve to map score to binary mortality outcome\n",
    "        # The logit equation is calibrated so a SNAPPE-II score of 50 corresponds to a 50% mortality rate\n",
    "        logit = -4.0 + 0.08 * row['snappe_score']\n",
    "        mortality_prob = 1.0 / (1.0 + np.exp(-logit))\n",
    "        row['mortality_probability'] = round(mortality_prob, 4)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Draw binary outcome (0 = Survived, 1 = Deceased) from a Bernoulli trial using the probability\n",
    "        row['mortality_outcome'] = int(np.random.binomial(1, mortality_prob))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        data.append(row)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    return pd.DataFrame(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "df = generate_dataset(5000)\n",
    "# Ensure directories exist\n",
    "os.makedirs('MachineLearning', exist_ok=True)\n",
    "df.to_csv('MachineLearning/neonatal_dataset.csv', index=False)\n",
    "print(\"Dataset generated and saved to 'MachineLearning/neonatal_dataset.csv'\")\n",
    "print(\"Class Distribution (0 = Survived, 1 = Deceased):\")\n",
    "print(df.groupby('mortality_outcome').size())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📊 Step 3: Feature Preprocessing & Scaling\n",
    "\n",
    "To feed numerical features to multi-layered neural networks (MLP) or Support Vector Machines (SVM), we **must scale the features** to have a mean of 0 and standard deviation of 1. \n",
    "\n",
    "Without scaling, features with high numeric magnitudes (e.g., `birth_weight_g` ranging from 500 to 4500) will dwarf features with small magnitudes (e.g., `lowest_serum_ph` ranging from 6.8 to 7.4) in Euclidean distance calculations and weight updates.\n",
    "\n",
    "We split the data into **80% training** and **20% testing** using stratified splits to keep class ratios consistent."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set output target variable (y)\n",
    "y = df['mortality_outcome']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set input predictor features (X)\n",
    "feature_cols = [\n",
    "    'birth_weight_g', 'gestational_age_weeks', 'sga', 'apgar_score_5min',\n",
    "    'mean_blood_pressure', 'lowest_temperature_celsius', 'po2_fio2_ratio',\n",
    "    'lowest_serum_ph', 'seizures', 'urine_output_ml_kg_hr',\n",
    "    'avg_heart_rate_bpm', 'lowest_spo2_percent'\n",
    "]\n",
    "X = df[feature_cols]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Stratify split preserves the same percentage of positive (mortality) cases in both subsets\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y, test_size=0.20, random_state=42, stratify=y\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fit standard scaler ONLY on training data to prevent data leakage from validation set\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Training set scaled feature shape: {X_train_scaled.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Validation set scaled feature shape: {X_test_scaled.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🧠 Step 4: Model 1 - Support Vector Machine (SVM) Classifier\n",
    "\n",
    "SVM draws an optimal boundary (hyperplane) that maximizes the margin between classes. We use the **Radial Basis Function (RBF) kernel** which projects features into high-dimensional Hilbert space to handle non-linear separation boundaries.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Platt Scaling for Probabilities\n",
    "By default, SVM yields distance-based decision scores instead of true probabilities. We set `probability=True` to train an internal logistic regression model (Platt Scaling) over the SVM outputs via internal cross-validation. This enables calibrated predictions via `predict_proba` which we need for bedside risk assessment."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Training RBF Support Vector Machine...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Parameters:\n",
    "# - C=1.0: Penalty multiplier for misclassifications (regularization parameter)\n",
    "# - gamma='scale': Kernel coefficient calculated as 1 / (n_features * X.var())\n",
    "# - probability=True: Enables Platt probability calibration\n",
    "svm_model = SVC(kernel='rbf', C=1.0, gamma='scale', probability=True, random_state=42)\n",
    "svm_model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate hard class predictions and continuous probabilities\n",
    "svm_preds = svm_model.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
    "svm_probs = svm_model.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Evaluate classifier diagnostics\n",
    "print(\"\\n================ SVM Classifier Evaluation ================\")\n",
    "print(f\"Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, svm_preds)*100:.2f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"F1-Score: {f1_score(y_test, svm_preds):.4f} (Harmonic mean of precision and recall)\")\n",
    "print(f\"ROC-AUC:  {roc_auc_score(y_test, svm_probs):.4f} (Discriminative power across thresholds)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nDetailed Classification Report:\")\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, svm_preds, target_names=['Survived', 'Deceased']))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Confusion Matrix:\")\n",
    "print(confusion_matrix(y_test, svm_preds))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🤖 Step 5: Model 2 - Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP) Neural Network\n",
    "\n",
    "The MLP is a feedforward Artificial Neural Network (ANN) that processes input features through hidden layer transformations to learn structural representations.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Network Topology\n",
    "- **Input Layer**: 12 neurons (matching the scaled features).\n",
    "- **Hidden Layer 1**: 64 neurons utilizing the Rectified Linear Unit (`relu`) activation function.\n",
    "- **Hidden Layer 2**: 32 neurons utilizing the `relu` activation function.\n",
    "- **Output Layer**: 1 neuron with a sigmoid activation function (mapping to binary probability).\n",
    "\n",
    "### Overfitting Protection (Early Stopping)\n",
    "We configure `early_stopping=True`. The algorithm holds out a random `10%` fraction of training data as an validation subset. If the loss on this validation set fails to decrease for `10` consecutive epochs, training is automatically aborted. This prevents the network from memorizing training data and guarantees clinical generalizability."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Training MLP Neural Network...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Parameters:\n",
    "# - hidden_layer_sizes=(64, 32): 2 hidden layers with 64 and 32 nodes respectively\n",
    "# - solver='adam': Stochastic gradient optimizer that adjusts learning rate per weight\n",
    "# - early_stopping=True: Validates performance on validation fraction to halt training early\n",
    "mlp_model = MLPClassifier(\n",
    "    hidden_layer_sizes=(64, 32),\n",
    "    activation='relu',\n",
    "    solver='adam',\n",
    "    max_iter=500,\n",
    "    early_stopping=True,\n",
    "    validation_fraction=0.1,\n",
    "    random_state=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "mlp_model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate predictions\n",
    "mlp_preds = mlp_model.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
    "mlp_probs = mlp_model.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Evaluate diagnostics\n",
    "print(\"\\n================ MLP Neural Network Evaluation ================\")\n",
    "print(f\"Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, mlp_preds)*100:.2f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"F1-Score: {f1_score(y_test, mlp_preds):.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f"ROC-AUC:  {roc_auc_score(y_test, mlp_probs):.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nDetailed Classification Report:\")\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, mlp_preds, target_names=['Survived', 'Deceased']))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Confusion Matrix:\")\n",
    "print(confusion_matrix(y_test, mlp_preds))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📈 Step 6: Diagnostic Visualization (ROC Curves)\n",
    "\n",
    "A Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC) curve plots the **True Positive Rate (Sensitivity)** against the **False Positive Rate (1 - Specificity)** across every classification probability threshold. \n",
    "\n",
    "The **Area Under the Curve (AUC)** score ranges from 0.5 (random guessing) to 1.0 (perfect prediction). A higher AUC represents a model that is robust and stable across clinical operating thresholds."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate ROC points and Area Under Curve (AUC) values\n",
    "fpr_svm, tpr_svm, _ = roc_curve(y_test, svm_probs)\n",
    "fpr_mlp, tpr_mlp, _ = roc_curve(y_test, mlp_probs)\n",
    "auc_svm = auc(fpr_svm, tpr_svm)\n",
    "auc_mlp = auc(fpr_mlp, tpr_mlp)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot curves using matplotlib\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6), dpi=100)\n",
    "plt.plot(fpr_svm, tpr_svm, label=f'RBF SVM (AUC = {auc_svm:.4f})', color='darkorange', lw=2)\n",
    "plt.plot(fpr_mlp, tpr_mlp, label=f'MLP Neural Net (AUC = {auc_mlp:.4f})', color='blue', lw=2)\n",
